 
<p>
If biometric tests are developed to detect sleepiness, and they are
used to stop professional drivers from driving, the financial loss
from being stopped occasionally
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/may/08/experts-divided-on-ethics-of-testing-and-punishing-tired-drivers">must fall on the companies</a>
they work for, or on the state &mdash;  not on the individual drivers.
<p>
This will lead us to a fight like the current one over
<a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2022-nov-feb.html#30_January_2023_(*While_blocking_paid_sick_leave,)">sick days for
train operator workers</a>.

